Package: ShatterSeek
Type: Package
Title: Comprehensive Chromoanagenesis Detection and Analysis from WGS Data
Version: 2.0.0
Date: 2025-01-18
Authors@R: c(
    person("Isidro", "Cortes-Ciriano", email = "isidrolauscher@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cph")),
    person("Ruibin", "Xi", role = "aut"),
    person("Extended Analysis Contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "your.email@example.com", comment = "Chromoplexy, chromosynthesis, advanced visualization, BND parsing"))
Maintainer: Extended Analysis Contributors <your.email@example.com>
Description: ShatterSeek detects and analyzes chromoanagenesis events (chromothripsis,
    chromoplexy, chromosynthesis) from whole-genome sequencing data. Originally developed
    for chromothripsis detection (Cortes-Ciriano et al., Nature Genetics 2020), this
    extended version adds comprehensive multi-mechanism detection, advanced visualization
    (genome dashboards, gGnome-style regional plots, circos plots), direct VCF input with
    BND/translocation parsing, breakpoint sequence analysis, and integrated classification.
    Supports multiple SV callers (Manta, Delly, DRAGEN, GRIDSS, LUMPY, Sniffles) and CNV
    callers (CNVkit, GATK, Control-FREEC, Canvas).
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0), methods, BiocGenerics, foreach, graph, S4Vectors
Imports: GenomicRanges, IRanges, MASS, ggplot2, grid, gridExtra
Suggests: VariantAnnotation, vcfR, circlize, BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19, BSgenome.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg38
